  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "If you have forgotten your SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) exam password, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Official SSC Website**: Go to the official SSC website (ssc.nic.in).\n\n2. **Click on 'Login'**: Find the login section for the SSC CGL exam.\n\n3. **Forgot Password**: Look for a link or option that says \"Forgot Password\" or \"Reset Password\" and click on it.\n\n4. **Provide Required Details**: You may need to enter details such as your registration number, date of birth, and possibly other verification information.\n\n5. **Follow Instructions**: After submitting the required information, follow the instructions sent to your registered email address or phone number to reset your password.\n\n6. **Create a New Password**: Once you receive the password reset link, you can create a new password.\n\n7. **Login with New Password**: After successfully resetting your password, return to the login page and enter your credentials with the new password.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, you can contact the SSC helpline or support for further assistance.",
